assertion_line: 87
expression: "snapshot_help(&[\"context\"])"
---
Inject project context into LLM prompts. Use to provide per-project instructions to agents.

Usage: normalize context [OPTIONS] [COMMAND]

Commands:
  context  Inject project context into LLM prompts. Use to provide per-project instructions to agents.
  migrate  Migrate old `.context.md` / `CONTEXT.md` files to the new `.normalize/context/` system.
  help     Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
      --pretty                     Human-friendly output with colors and formatting
      --compact                    Compact output without colors (overrides TTY detection)
      --jsonl                      Output one JSON object per line (for arrays)
      --json                       Output machine-readable JSON
      --jq <jq>                    Filter output through jq expression
      --input-schema               Print JSON Schema of the subcommand's input parameters and exit
      --output-schema              Print JSON Schema of the subcommand's return type and exit
      --params-json <params-json>  Provide all parameters as a JSON object instead of individual flags
      --root <root>                Root directory for hierarchy walk (default: cwd)
      --match <match>              Match context against KEY=VALUE pair (repeatable)
      --stdin                      Read context JSON from stdin
      --prefix <prefix>            Namespace stdin JSON under this prefix
      --all                        Return all context entries without filtering
      --from <from>                Context directory name inside .normalize/ (default: context)
      --list                       Show source file paths only, not content
      --file <file>                Load a structured file into caller context as PREFIX=PATH (repeatable; supports .json, .toml, .yaml/.yml)
  -h, --help                       Print help
  -V, --version                    Print version
